					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of a quarter <hi rend="italic">(vēli)</hi> of land after its purchase for 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold, by Pūvaṉ Kaṇṇaṉ of <hi rend="bold">Neḍumpuṟaiyār</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Malai-nāḍu</hi>, for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭattu-Paramasvāmi at Tirukkuḍamukkil. The writing is similar to that of No. 96 below. This is probably assignable to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
